      • resizeStack

        public Stack<E> resizeStack​(int newLength)
        Changes the stack size. It should be used if you know the approximate number of items that will be stored in the stack.

        The method returns this stack for fluent style code.

        Parameters:
        newLength - new actual length of stack
        Returns:
        this

      • pop

        public java.util.Optional<E> pop()
        Retrieves an element from the top of this stack and wraps it with Optional. If this stack is empty, the method will return an empty Optional instance.
        Returns:
        an element from the top of this stack

      • popStack

        public java.util.Optional<Stack<E>> popStack​(int length)
        Retrieves the length elements from the top of this stack as a new stack and wraps it with Optional. If this stack contains less than length elements, the method will return an empty Optional instance.
        Parameters:
        length - the length of the new stack
        Returns:
        the new stack
